40:23.290 --> 40:25.330
GROVER: Christian.
His name was Christian.

40:25.330 --> 40:28.950
♪ Leave your heart outside ♪

40:28.950 --> 40:32.330
♪ Leave it all and let it go ♪

40:32.330 --> 40:35.790
♪ It might come back sometime ♪

40:35.790 --> 40:38.990
♪ You know, you never know ♪

40:38.990 --> 40:41.700
♪ Before you say good-bye ♪

40:41.700 --> 40:47.750
♪ You better know
where you’re going to go... ♪

40:47.750 --> 40:49.700
WOMAN:
Lou.

40:50.410 --> 40:51.330
Oh, hey.

40:51.330 --> 40:54.750
Hey. I hear this is your
last session with us.

40:54.750 --> 40:57.250
Yeah, um...

40:57.250 --> 41:01.990
I’m sorry. I should have
told you myself. Um...

41:02.990 --> 41:05.990
You guys have really
helped me a lot,

41:05.990 --> 41:07.410
um, but...

41:07.410 --> 41:13.200
I kind of feel like I’m not
gonna be able to move on

41:13.200 --> 41:16.450
as long as I’m here.

41:17.410 --> 41:20.620
Too many bad memories here
in Chicago.

41:20.620 --> 41:25.990
So, where are you going to go?

41:26.870 --> 41:28.990
I don’t know.

41:30.160 --> 41:32.620
But you know what?

41:32.620 --> 41:33.990
Wherever that is,

41:33.990 --> 41:37.950
I’m gonna make damn sure
that it’s a hell of a lot warmer

41:37.950 --> 41:40.580
than it is here, okay?

41:41.990 --> 41:43.410
So, um...

41:43.410 --> 41:46.000
Hey, thanks.

41:46.000 --> 41:47.580
Thanks a lot.

41:47.580 --> 41:53.450
♪ So we’re told ♪

